\"88\" height=\"31\"/></a>\t\t\t\t\t\t</li>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div style=\"clear:both\"></div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t\t<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgPageParseReport\":{\"smw\":{\"limitreport-intext-parsertime\":0},\"limitreport\":{\"cputime\":\"0.072\",\"walltime\":\"0.134\",\"ppvisitednodes\":{\"value\":139,\"limit\":1000000},\"ppgeneratednodes\":{\"value\":525,\"limit\":1000000},\"postexpandincludesize\":{\"value\":2228,\"limit\":2097152},\"templateargumentsize\":{\"value\":390,\"limit\":2097152},\"expansiondepth\":{\"value\":4,\"limit\":40},\"expensivefunctioncount\":{\"value\":0,\"limit\":100},\"timingprofile\":[\"100.00%  114.614      1 -total\",\" 57.93%   66.397      1 Template:Monsters_with_spell\",\" 29.46%   33.762      1 Template:Version031\",\" 28.42%   32.575      1 Template:Version\",\"  3.22%    3.687      1 Template:Glyph\",\"  1.30%    1.489      2 Template:Source_ref\",\"  1.15%    1.315      1 Template:Flavour\",\"  1.00%    1.143      2 Template:Yellow\",\"  0.98%    1.126      2 Template:Red\",\"  0.85%    0.973      1 Template:LightRed\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240916112455\",\"ttl\":86400,\"transientcontent\":false}}});});</script><script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":229});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{version031}}\n{{flavour|Taints a targeted creature's ability to cast spells. Casting a spell while afflicted with this condition causes the target to lose access to their magic, briefly preventing them from casting any further spells.}}\n\n'''Sap Magic''' is a monsters-only spell. Against players, it inflicts the {{Yellow|Sap}} status for 20-30 turns.<ref>{{source ref|0.31.0|beam.cc|3660}}</ref> When you have this status, successfully casting any spell gives you the {{Red|-Cast}} status for 3-5 turns.<ref>{{source ref|0.31.0|spl-cast.cc|1018}}</ref> Getting hit by Sap Magic multiple times will extend its duration (max. 50 turns). You can cure both Sap and -Cast with a [[potion of cancellation]].\n\nMonsters with [[Spell slot flags#Wizard flag|wizardly]] spells can be affected by Sap Magic too. They receive an [[antimagic]] penalty, which could make them falter when they try to cast spells.\n\n{{monsters with spell}}\n\n==Strategy==\n\nBeing in Sap status essentially means that you will be in a cycle of only being able to cast one spell every ~4 turns, until that status times out or you use a potion of cancellation. Thus, if you are primarily a spellcaster:\n*Make that one, periodic spell count. If you kill or escape from all [[demonspawn warmonger]]s in [[LOS]], use a potion of cancellation.\n*If you can't do that, have a robust plan to escape from pursuing enemies until the status wears off.\n\n==History==\n*Prior to [[0.28]], the Sap status had a 50% chance to increase your spell failure penalty each time when you cast a spell. There were three levels:\n**{{Yellow|-Wiz}}: spell failure rate increased by 12%;\n**{{LightRed|-Wiz}}: spell failure rate increased by 24%;\n**{{Red|-Wiz}}: spell failure rate increased by 36%.\n**Also, the spell had a 30% chance to have no effect when cast, despite being otherwise irresistible.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n[[Category:Monster spells]]"}